<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Law Meeting Participants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua)-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that administering a country by law is not only a sign
of civilization and progress for a society, but also a powerful
guarantee of long-term stability.
</P>
<P>
He made this remark when he met with participants who attended
a conference on law today, which was sponsored by the China Law
Society.
</P>
<P>
He said that this is a basic policy of China, as Deng Xiaoping
advocated the development of socialist democracy and the
strengthening of the socialist legal system, beginning with the
3rd Plenary Session of the 11th Congress of the CPC Central
Committee in 1978.
</P>
<P>
He noted that without socialist democracy and a legal system
there would be no modernization drive in China. Therefore, he
noted, the Party, leading officials in particular, should make an
effort to promote socialist democracy and the legal system and
improve their style of leadership and management level.
</P>
<P>
Legal workers are an important force in promoting China's
democracy and its legal system, he said, adding that he hopes they
continue to work to resolve major issues under the guidance of
Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics,
and better serve the country's reform drive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
