<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Send Mission to Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union(EU) is to
send a fact-finding mission to Belarus on January 26 to study the
legality of last November's constitutional referendum and the
circumstances under which it took place, the Dutch presidency
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The mission, led by former Dutch Justice Minister Aad Kosto,
will also examine the role of the opposition and the independent
media in the Belarussian political process.
</P>
<P>
Western countries believe the referendum greatly expanded
the powers of Belarussian President Alexander Lukashenko, who
favours a renewed economic union with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Moscow has strongly opposed NATO's planned expansion eastward
and has said it may have to respond by creating its own new bloc.
</P>
<P>
The decision to send a fact-finding mission to Belarus was
taken by EU foreign ministers during their meeting here on
Monday. The team will report to the next foreign ministers'
council meeting on February 24.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
