<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China International Electronic Commerce Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- China's first international
electronic commerce center opened in Beijing today, according to
minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi, who made
the announcement at a national conference on foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the establishment of China International Electronic
Commerce Center and China Trade Network marks a new step toward
more intensive use of information for foreign trade and economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The center and the network will also provide an effective
channel for the world to get to know China, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
To enhance the role of information is an important task in
promoting the development of China's foreign trade, Wu explained,
noting that enterprises and foreign trade administrators should
increase the pace of entering the network, and to gradually link
up with banks, customs offices, tax offices, departments in charge
of foreign exchange and insurance, and commercial organizations in
foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
She also encouraged the connection of the new center with the
UN trade information network and other international trade
networks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
