<HEADLINE> Direct Access To Internet for China's Overseas Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scholars studying
overseas wanting to find out about an investment policy for a
domestic high-tech development zone can now get the information
directly through the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The network includes information about overseas scholars and
their work, policies about returning home and working for the
country, lists of major colleges and universities, scientific
research institutes, and enterprises, and information about key
subjects and labs in China.
</P>
<P>
Official from the Chinese Service Center for Scholarly Exchange
(CSCSE), which is in charge of the network, say they will make it
a professional information resource center for overseas scholars
and a "technology information board".
</P>
<P>
Sites will also be set up in Chinese embassies and consulates,
CSCSE branches, and groups of overseas scholars in foreign
countries to speed information access.
</P>
<P>
Founded in early 1994 by CSCSE, the information network has
provided information about overseas scholars and domestic
companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
