<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Symposium On Deng Xiaoping's Theories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on Deng Xiaoping's
theories opened in Beijing today to mark the fifth anniversary of
his famous south China tour, one that added great impetus to the
country's reform and opening up drive.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was hosted by the Party School of the Communist
Party of China's Central Committee, with 60 prominent academics
and journalists present.
</P>
<P>
Participants said they agreed that the keynote speech Deng made
during his southern visit, along with the 14th CPC national
congress in late 1992, indicated that China's reforms, opening up,
and modernization drive had entered a new phase.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Deng pointed out that a socialist country can
also have a market economy, one that is not identical to
capitalism, providing a theoretical basis for "building a
socialist market economic system".
</P>
<P>
The participants said Deng's speech integrated Marxism-Leninism
and Mao Zedong thought with the reality of China's reform and
development, and demonstrated the veteran leader's enormous
political and theoretical courage.
</P>
<P>
They said they attribute China's rapid growth over recent years
to the powerful guidance of Deng's theories, as well as the
correct and firm leadership of the Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at its core, and that a careful re-examination of
Deng's 1992 speech in current circunstances can further promote
research on and publicity about Deng's theories of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and greatly benefit the
country's economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
