<DOCNO> XIE19970122.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Building Natural Gas Treatment Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The foundation of a natural
gas treatment plant was laid today in Shanghai, China's largest
industrial and economic center.
</P>
<P>
This marks the beginning of construction of the East Sea Pinghu
Petroleum and Gas Project, a joint effort of the Ministry of
Geology and Mineral Resource, China National Offshore Oil
Corporation and the city of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase of the project includes construction of a
offshore platform, drilling of 13 oil and gas wells, the laying of
365-km of natural gas pipeline, the construction of a natural gas
treatment plant in Nanhui, the laying of 305-km of crude oil
pipeline, and the building of a crude oil transmission station in
Daishan, in Zhejiang Province. Total cost is estimated at five
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Natural Gas Treatment Plant of Shanghai will cover an area
of 130,000 square meters and will mainly be used to process
natural gas from the pipeline to supply the Pudong New Area of
Shanghai. The plant has a daily handling capacity of 1.6 million
cu.m. of natural gas and is expected to be operational at the end
of 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
