<HEADLINE> China To Combat Air Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- At the 10th session of China's
State Council's 3rd Environmental Protection Commission today,
State Councillor Song Jian called on the country to take steps to
prevent air pollution from going from bad to worse.
</P>
<P>
"The quality of the air has a close tie with people's health,"
Song, who is director of the environmental commission of the State
Council, noted.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the conference say that sulfur dioxide has been a
major factor in the deteriorating environment, causing air
pollution and acid rain in west and south China.
</P>
<P>
China plans to study air pollution in 47 major cities,
including Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin, Shenyang, Guangzhou and
Xi'an, with the first ten expected to hand in weekly reports on
local air pollution this June.
</P>
<P>
"Its aim is to reflect the current environmental situation in
large and medium-sized cities, and solicit comments from the
public," Song said.
</P>
<P>
The deteriorating environment and rapid population growth are
becoming serious threats to resources and environment, and to
China's sustained economic development. China has to take steps to
fight environmental pollution, such as closing small enterprises
which seriously pollute the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
