<HEADLINE> Deceased Widow Of Veteran Chinese Journalist Honored Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A memorial ceremony was held
in Shanghai today in honor of Shen Cuizhen, who passed away in
Shanghai on January 12, at the age of 96.
</P>
<P>
She was the wife of Zou Taofen, one of China's best-known
patriotic journalists, who died some five decades ago.
</P>
<P>
Today's ceremony was attended by Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua,
Shen's son, and his wife, and sons and daughters. President Jiang
Zemin asked leading officials from Shanghai to convey his
heartfelt condolences to the family of the deceased.
</P>
<P>
In the 1940s, with the help of Soong Ching Ling, the wife of
Sun Yat Sen, and Deng Yingchao, the wife of late Premier Zhou
Enlai, Shen devoted herself to the War of Resistance against
Japanese Aggression and the national liberation movement.
</P>
<P>
After new China was founded in 1949, Shen went on to work
for social welfare in the country, along with with Soong Ching Ling.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premiers Zhu Rongji, Li Lanqing, and Wu Bangguo sent
wreaths to the ceremony, which was attended by Municipal Party
Secretary Huang Ju and Mayor Xu Kuangdi.  
</P>
