The MV Bukoba, a property of the Tanzania Railways Corporation
(TRC), capsized on Lake Victoria on May 21, 1996 on its way to
Mwanza from Bukoba.
</P>
<P>
The TPC official said other stamps to be printed by the
company will feature tourist attractions in east Africa, Tanzania
coastal birds, and traditional weapons.
</P>
