<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded today
outside a Planned Parenthood clinic in central Washington,
D.C. early this morning less than a kilometer from the White House.
</P>
<P>
There were 10-15 patients and staff inside the abortion clinic
when the bomb went off at 7.45 a.m. EST (1245 GMT), but there were
no reports of damage or injuries.
</P>
<P>
