used a balanced offense and defense in the second half to overtake
the visitors 56-54 on Bateer's basket with 13:40 seconds to play.
</P>
<P>
Then scores tied three times until forward Huang Yunlong of
Guangdong was foulded and hit one of two free throws to send the
game into the overtime, 83-83.
</P>
<P>
Xue Limin hit 8 of his 12 points in the extral time and led
Beijing to the victory.
</P>
<P>
Li Chunjiang scored a game-high 44 points, including 10 of 17
in the three-pointer range for the Tigers, which now place fifth
on the rankings with 9-7.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets and the Liaoning Hunter share the league lead with
14-2, followed by the Shandong Flaming Bulls (12-4) and the
Shanghai Oriental (11-5). 
