<HEADLINE> Xiamen Establishes International Commodity Auction Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen International Commodity
Auction Center, a state-level auction center, has been established
in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Jointly run by Xiamen Material Supplies Group and Xiamen
Electronics and Machinery Equipment Corporation, the center will
arrange auctions of confiscated goods (including motor vehicles),
and goods without owners and mortgages.
</P>
<P>
It will also arrange auctions entrusted by legal persons of
enterprises and other customers. The auctioned goods include means
of subsistence, second-hand motor vehicles, artistic works, real
estate and intangible assets.
</P>
<P>
The center is also the first big auction center approved by the
Ministry of Internal Trade after the adoption of China's Auction
Law last year.
</P>
<P>
China so far has five state-level auction centers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
