<HEADLINE> Nepali Officials Charged with Corruption in Adoption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Three officials of Nepal's
Home Ministry are facing corruption charges after they permitted a
foreign couple to adopt two orphans, the official news agency RSS
said today.
</P>
<P>
Under Nepal's law, one foreign couple are prohibited from
adopting more than one child in the country.
</P>
<P>
A governmental anti-corruption agency today filed a law suit at
the appellate court here against Secretary Padma Pokhrel, Joint
Secretary Ganesh Bhattarai and Under Secretary Koah Nemwang of the
Home Ministry on charges of committing corruption due to their
involvement in the double adoption case, the RSS reported.
</P>
<P>
The Commission for Investigation of Abuse of Authority (CIAA)
accused the three of allowing a Spanish couple, who had adopted a
boy from an orphanage in the eastern district of Morang two years
ago, to adopt a second child from the same orphanage last year.
</P>
<P>
The CIAA also asked the Home Ministry to take administrative
action against the Chief District Officer of the eastern district
of Morang, who recommended the second adoption by the Spanish
couple, the RSS added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
