<HEADLINE> Hainan Builds Australian Fresh Water Lobster Breeding Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction is underway on the
Australian Freshwater Lobster Breeding Center in the city of
Qiongshan in south China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
The center, covering an area of 67 hectares, is being built by
Hainan Feiteng Development Corporation.
</P>
<P>
So far, 6.6 hectares of lobster ponds and a one-hectare
hatching pond have been completed, and 350,000 young lobsters are
growing well in the ponds.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to complete the ponds by the end of
next year and build a lobster fodder factory with annual
production capacity of 30 tons, as well as a factory to process
lobster products.
</P>
<P>
Apart from building the center, the corporation will also carry
out trial breeding of new lobster varieties such as seven-color
fancy lobster, monosex lobster and soft-shell lobster. 
</P>
