<HEADLINE> Egrets Return to Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of egrets have
returned to Huwei Mountain in the urban area of Xiamen, an island
city and the original home of egrets for many years in east
China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
To the delight of environmental protection experts, they are
the same egrets lost half a month ago from Dayu Island, a nature
reserve in the sea about 1,000 meters away from Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Catching a sight of thousands of egrets on the mountain, a
local resident reported the news to the city's environment
protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
A group of bird experts and post graduate students from
biological department of Xiamen Uninversity carried out an
investigation in the mountain area.
</P>
<P>
When the team went to the deep forest area, thousands of
grey-white colored, long and sharp mouthed, sea gull like egrets
scattered, singing and dancing.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, covered with silks trees and pines, will be a
nature park according to the city's development plan. And nearby
Yuandang Lake has fish and shrimps which could serve as food for
the egrets.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen was famous for its tens of thousands of egrets living in
the island, and had been called egret island in the past.
</P>
<P>
However, with the economic development of the city, the
ecological environment had deteriorated and many egrets moved to
the Dayu Island. The city established the Dayu Island nature
reserve to protect the egrets there.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of the environment, bird experts said,
egrets returned to the island to spend their winter. If the birds
feel the environment suitable for them, they will settle on the
mountain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970122.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
