<HEADLINE> East China Province Developing Trade Contacts With Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province will
make an effort this year to draw more Taiwanese investors and
increase trade with Taiwan, according to a provincial government
official.
</P>
<P>
He said that by November of last year 370 Taiwan-funded
enterprises had been approved, with investment of more than 2.15
billion US dollars, and that about half of the top 100 Taiwanese
enterprises have made inspection tours of Fujian, with 24 having
invested in over 30 projects in the province.
</P>
<P>
In addition to looking for investment from Taiwan, trade groups
have visited Taiwan. In 1996, about 70 of them went to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In October, the ministries of Communications and Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation gave Fujian province its blessing and
named the cities of Fuzhou and Xiamen as experimental ports for
direct travel across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Fujian now has 54 ports and more than 400 berths, 22 of which
are deep water. The cities of Fuzhou and Xiamen have built
passenger terminals and are now among China's top ten ports.
</P>
