<HEADLINE> HKSAR Chief Executive Forms New Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
today announced the organization of his office.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said that Mrs. Fanny Law will be the Director of
Tung's Office and assist Tung in formulating the policy agenda for
the HKSAR Government. She is also responsible for the day-to-day
administration of the Office.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Andrew Lo and Stanley Shen, both from the Orient
Overseas (International) Ltd, are chosen as special assistants to
Tung. They will provide general support and information services
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Law will be assisted initially by Philip Yung, the
district officer (Central and Western), and a team of 14 executive
and general support staff. Yung will join Tung's Office after the
Lunar New Year, while the other seconded staff will build up
gradually as suitable officers become available.
</P>
<P>
"I am pleased that the Hong Kong Government had agreed to
second 29 officers to assist me in the transitional period," Tung
said. "The secondment will be temporary in nature and will lapse
on July 1, 1997."
</P>
<P>
Staff to be seconded will include Administrative Officers,
Executive Officers and general support staff. They will take leave
of absence from the Hong Kong Government and will work under the
direction of, and be accountable to, the Chief Executive,
according to the announcement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
