<HEADLINE> Soeharto to Name 200 Millionth Indonesian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The 200 millionth Indonesian,
expected to be born on February 4, will be named by President
Soeharto, a senior official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
State Minister of Population Haryono Suyono said that to
qualify for the honor, the baby has to come from legally married
parents.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the minister said, the baby should have a mother
who got married at an age over 20 and had her first baby at that
age limit.
</P>
<P>
"The baby should not be born by cesarean section also," Suyono
said, adding that on February 4 at least 8,182 babies are expected
to be born.
</P>
<P>
He said that on February 5, the president will be officially
informed of the country's 200 millionth citizen.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Suyono said the 200 millionth baby will get a surprise
present from the government.
</P>
<P>
He also said each province can nominate the baby born on that
date in their locality.
</P>
<P>
Adding to the qualification, Suyono said the baby's mother
during her pregnancy should have undergone regular medical checkup
in a health care center with either a doctor or midwife.  
</P>
</TEXT>
