<HEADLINE> Nigeria Arrests 22 Bomb Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-two people have been
arrested in connection with the series of bomb blasts that hit
Lagos in the last few months, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Godwin Ugbo, the acting spokesman of the Defense
Headquarters, said here on Tuesday that the arrests were made
by a special investigation team set up by the Defense
Headquarters, but he gave no details of the arrest.
</P>
<P>
