<HEADLINE> Ajax to Name Morten Olsen as New Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMSTERDAM, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Danish soccer veteran Morten
Olsen will replace Louis van Gaal as coach of Dutch powerhouse
Ajax, a newspaper reported here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The appointment is ``almost a done deal,'' but the club is
delaying the announcement until its players return from a training
session in Spain, said the national daily Algemeen Dagblad.
</P>
<P>
the Rotterdam-based newspaper said the 47-year-old Dane will
take over at Ajax in July.
</P>
<P>
Van Gaal took over at Ajax in 1991 and guided the club to the
UEFA Cup title in 1992 and the European Champions Cup title in
1995. He anounced in October that he would be leaving the club at
the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
Olsen was Denmark's captain during the European Championship in
France in 1982 and in the World Cup in Mexico in 1986.
</P>
<P>
A midfielder/libero, Olsen played for Vordingborg IF and B1901
in Demmark, Belgian clubs Cercles Bruges, Racing White, and
Anderlecht, and German club FC Cologne.
</P>
<P>
He had moderate success as a coach at Danish club Broendby IF
and FC Cologne, where he was fired from both jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
