<HEADLINE> Sampras Tumbles into Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
was extended to five sets before beating Spaniard Albert Costa to
enter the semi-finals of the Australian Open tennis tournament in
Melbourne, Australia, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, the 1994 champion, won 6-3, 6-7, 6-1, 3-6, 6-2 and
will face Thomas Muster of Austria in the semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Sampras slammed 23 aces in the match, which was his second
straight five-setter in the tournament. He overcame Slovakia's
Dominik Hrbaty in Monday's fourth round. 
</P>
