<HEADLINE> Thailand to Free 11 Cambodians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will release 11
Cambodians, who are suspected of piracy, at the request of the
Cambodian government, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government has agreed to free the Cambodians, who are
actually Cambodian officials, to show goodwill toward Cambodia,
the Bangkok Post quoted Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Thailand earlier freed some Vietnamese suspects for the same
reason, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The 11 Cambodians were captured by the Thai Navy when they were
allegedly robbing a Thai fishing boat on September 22 last year.
They were charged with illegal possession of weapons, illegal
entry, robbery and resisting arrest, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Diplomats at the Cambodian Embassy here had said the Cambodians
were officials who tried to search a Thai boat which was fishing
near Cambodia's Koh Kong Province.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats denied that the officials had committed robbery.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
