<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed
on the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index continued to decline, falling by another 10.78
points to close at 2240.01 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was 348.76 million units, valued at
630.25 million Singapore dollars (about 450.17 million U.S.
dollars). Advances led declines 215 to 138, while 243 other
counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
CSH was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 98.03 million units. It was followed by FHTK which had
13.21 million shares traded. The local computer maker IPC
Corporation saw 13.14 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
YHS led the gainers of the day, rising by 40 cents to finish at
5.45 Singapore dollars. Creative 50, Oriental Holdings and the
United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign each gained 30 cents to close
at 16.3, 11, and 16.9 Singapore dollars respectively. The Gentings
was 25 cents higher at 9.6 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) and the Singapore
Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign shared the top spot on the losers'
list as each of them fell by 50 cents to end at 16.4 and 28
Singapore dollars respectively. F&AMP;N declined by 30 cents to 13.6
Singapore dollars, while Cerebos was 20 cents lower at 10.4
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
