<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indo-Sri Lanka Joint Commission Meeting Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A joint communique issued at
the conclusion of the third session of the Indo-Lanka Joint
Commission here said today that the successful conclusion of the
third session would help facilitate cooperation between the two
countries in a number of vital areas.
</P>
<P>
The session, which was held on January 20-22, reviewed the work
of the sub-commissions of the joint commission on trade, finance
and investments; cultural and educational matters and on science
and technology, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The session was co-chaired by Indian Minister of External
Affairs Inder Kumar Gujral and Sri Lankan Minister of Foreign
Affairs Lakshman Kadirgamar.
</P>
<P>
It said the two ministers signed an agreement for the promotion
and protection of investment to generate investment flow between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
A cultural exchange program under the aegis of the
sub-commission on cultural and educational matters and a program
of cooperation under the aegis of the sub-commission on science
and technology were also signed by senior representatives of the
two governments.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers discussed a wide range of
international and regional issues and briefed each other on the
developments in their respective countries, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
The liberalization of the Sri Lankan economy, balancing of
trade, reduction of tariffs and removal of non-tariff barriers
were among the matters discussed.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed issues affecting Indian and Sri Lankan
fishermen in each other's waters and agreed that the two
governments would hold consultations whenever necessary.
</P>
<P>
The communique added that the Indian foreign minister also
announced the grant of 50 million Indian rupees as a contribution
to the Sri Lankan government's rehabilitation program in the north
and east.
</P>
<P>
The commission was set up in 1991. Its first and second
sessions have been held in India.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
