<HEADLINE> Japanese Firm Opens Regional Head office in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Omron Corporation, a Japanese
manufacturer of factory automation systems and control, opened a
regional head office in Hong Kong on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The head office is responsible for the corporation's business
in the Chinese mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The office, also named Omron (China) Group Co., Ltd., will
provide overall managerial support to 12 Omron group companies
now operating in the region, including nine in the Chinese
mainland, two in Hong Kong and one in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
According to Hideo Akaike, director of the Strategy Planning
Department of the corporation, up to now Omron has pursued its
overall management in the Chinese mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan
from Japan.
</P>
<P>
But, he said, Omron decided to establish this office after
reflecting on the mounting necessity to establish a management
center in the region due to the increasing growth and development
of complementary links of business and trade between the Chinese
mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said that Omron also aims to strengthen and expand its
business in the region by making more efficient the management
function of Omron (China) Co. Ltd., the Beijing-based Chinese
central office, Omron Electronics Asia LTD. in Hong Kong, as well
as Omron Taiwan Electronic Inc. in Taibei.
</P>
<P>
Omron expects total sales in the region in the fiscal year 1996
 to be around 27 billion Japanese yen (228.81 million
U.S. dollars), rising to 40 billion yen (338.98 million dollars)
in fiscal year 1997 and growing to 50 billion yen (423.73 million
dollars) by the year 2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
