<DOCNO> XIE19970122.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Rejects Kanu's Offer to Play Against Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Football Association
has rejected Kanu Nwankwo's offer to play for Super Eagles in
April's World Cup qualifer against Guinea, local media reported
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the association, Abdulmumuni Aminu, was quoted
as saying at a press conference on Tuesday that Kanu is
recuperating very fast after his recent heart surgery in the
United States, but still his health condition doesn't allow him to
play in the game.
</P>
<P>
The association wants him to be fully fit before inviting him
to the Super Eagles, the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
Abudlmumuni Aminu was just back from a trip to the United
States, where he transfered the 50,000 U.S. dollars promised to
Kanu by the Nigerian Head of State, General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Kanu, who led Nigeria's Under-23 team to a gold medal at the
Centennial Olympic Games in Atlanta, the United States last
August, was later found with a heart defect and underwent a heart
surgery.
</P>
<P>
He is the African Footballer of the Year for 1996, the eighth
Best World Player of the Year for 1996 by the World Soccer
magazine.
</P>
<P>
He was recently voted the world's sixth best player by the
Federation of International Football Associations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
