<HEADLINE> Chinese mainland, Taiwan Achieve Progress at Direct Shipping Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The shipping sectors of the
Chinese mainland and Taiwan today reached consensus on technical
issues concerning the direct shipping between the two selected
ports of Fuzhou and Xiamen of the Chinese mainland, and the
Kaohsiung Port in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The consensus was reached at a meeting jointly held here today
by the Association for Shipping Exchanges Across the Taiwan
Straits from the Chinese mainland and the Taiwan Strait Shipping
Association.
</P>
<P>
According to a news release from the association of the Chinese
 mainland, the meeting between the representatives of the shipping
 sectors across the straits achieved progress that had been
expected by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the two sides signed a minute on the
direct shipping services at the meeting which proceeded in a
businesslike and harmonious atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Meng Guangju, chairman of the association of the mainland, said
that the non-governmental consultations between the shipping
sectors across the straits are beneficial, adding that they will
play an active role in promoting direct shipping business between
the Chinese mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the two-way direct shipping would
materialize in the near future so as to meet growing trade demands
across the straits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
