<HEADLINE> HK Soccer Team to Play PSV Eindhoven </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The newly-established Hong
Kong soccer team will take on the Dutch first division side of PSV
Eindhoven in the Nike Challenge Cup set for Friday in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The one-match event, organized by the Hong Kong Football
Association, is to be held at the Hong Kong Stadium.
</P>
<P>
PSV Eindhoven is to field a strong line-up which includes Dutch
internationals Arthur Numan, Philip Cocu, Wim Jonk and Jaap Stam,
who are members of the Dutch national team preparing for the
qualification tournament for the World Cup in 1998.
</P>
