<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Regional Minimum Wage to Be Increased </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The regional minimum wage in
Indonesia will be increased by an average 10.07 percent starting
April 1, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"The new regional minimum wage will cover 95.32 percent of the
daily minimum needs," said Minister of Manpower Abdul Latief after
meeting with President Soeharto at the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
The new regional minimum wage, he said, will be applied in all
the provinces.
</P>
<P>
Based on the new regulation, the country's workers will receive
a salary ranging from 106,500 rupiah (44.38 U.S. dollars) to
235,900 rupiah (98.3 dollars) per month.
</P>
<P>
With the new decree, the minimum wage for workers in Central
Sulawesi and East Nusatenggara Province will increase to 106,500
rupiah per month, still the lowest minimum wage in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, workers in Batam, a special economic zone in Riau
Province, will get the highest minimum wage in the country, which
is 235,900 rupiah per month, while Jakarta workers will get
172,500 rupiah (71.9 dollars) per month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
