<HEADLINE> Australian Airlines to Add More Flights to HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Australian airline Qantas
will operate 10 additional flights between Hong Kong and the
Australian east coast in February.
</P>
<P>
The flights will meet the traditional high travel demand during
the Chinese Lunar New Year season and will add about 4,200 seats
to the 24 flights already offered each week.
</P>
<P>
According to the airline, services have been scheduled to offer
six flights southbound from Hong Kong to Brisbane, Cairns and
Sydney. Four northbound services will be added after the Chinese
Lunar New Year.
</P>
<P>
Alan Loke, Qantas Group's general manager, said the additional
services would provide travelers visiting friends and relatives in
Australia with a wider choice of flights.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Lunar New Year is a very important time for
many of our customers, adding that Qantas recognizes that many
people travel during this period and its additional flights will
help ensure that families can spend the New Year together.
</P>
<P>
Qantas will use six of the 10 flights to supplement freight
capacity between Australia and Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
