<HEADLINE> Arafat Briefs AL on Hebron Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority(PNA) President Yasser Arafat today consulted the Arab
League(AL) on the Palestinian position on the peace process and a
vision for the future after the Hebron accord.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who arrived here this morning, briefed AL Secretary
General Esmat Abdel Meguid on the details of the implementation of
the Israeli troop pullout from Hebron and the peace process in the
coming phases, according to the Egyptian MENA news agency.
</P>
<P>
The AL chief will then passed on the message to delegates of
the Arab countries, according to Palestinian sources earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader will hand over to Meguid a copy of the
Hebron redeployment protocol, which is to be kept with the
Cairo-based League General Secretariat, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the PNA chief extended his thanks to Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak for his support to the Palestinian stand
and their rights, in their first meeting since the PA took control
of most of the West Bank city of Hebron in a landmark deal with
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed the latest development of the Mideast
peace process and the implementation of the Hebron deal.
</P>
<P>
Arafat acquainted Mubarak of the details of the just-concluded
agreement and raise other issues in the transitional phase and
about the final status in the upcoming negotiations with Israel,
according to MENA.
</P>
<P>
The Hebron agreement came after four months of hard bargainings
between the PNA and Israel, pushed by tortuous mediations involving
the United states,the European Union, Egypt and Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two sides will resume talks on a
number of other issues immediately after the redeployment and
start the final status talks within two months.
</P>
<P>
The PNA leader arrived here from Rome, where he
addressed a conference of the Socialist International and had
talks with Prime Minister Romano Prodi and President Oscar Liugi
Scalfaro. 
</P>
</TEXT>
