<HEADLINE> Macao Issues Stamp of Lunar Year of Ox </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Macao will issue the stamp of the
Chinese lunar year, the Year of Ox, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.5 million pieces of the stamp, which depicts the
head of a huge buffalo with a face value of 5.5 patacas (about 70
U.S. cents), will be issued, which is three times the number of
the Year of Rat stamps issued in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Macao Posts and Telecommunications
Department said that all the 1.5 million pieces have been booked
even before the stamps go to the stalls.
</P>
<P>
The department said that it will increase the number of various
stamps to be issued this year by 20 percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 sets of stamps will be issued in Macao in 1997.
They include Lucky Number, Boat People, Drunken Dragon Festival,
Legends and Myths -- Gods of Protection, Balconies of Macao,
Chinese Traditional Fans and Fong Soi.  
</P>
