<HEADLINE> Flu Kills 116 in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A flu outbreak has so far killed
116 people in 14 of the 47 prefectures in Japan this winter,
according to a survey conducted Tuesday by the daily Mainichi
Shimbun.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims, either died of the virus or its resulting
complications, are more than 60 years old with weak immunity, said
the survey.
</P>
<P>
Even patients of younger ages had a high fever and had to stay
in bed for a week when they were infected with the flu virus,
which is more proliferous this year.
</P>
<P>
The population infected with the flu has reached more than
700,000 nationwide, and Japan's Ministry of Health and Welfare is
calling for stepping up precautious measures against the disease.
</P>
</TEXT>
