<HEADLINE> Most Conventions Applicable to Macao to Pass Through: Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
here today that most current world conventions applicable to Macao
will pass through 1999.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xi'an, counselor of the Chinese side on the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group (JLG), told reporters after
meeting with his Portuguese counterpart that any current world
conventions and bodies that are conducive to Macao's economic
growth and social stability and suit the status of Macao will enjoy
 the support of the Chinese side in their renewal after 1999.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side is currently studying the list provided by
the Portuguese side last December on the world bodies or
conventions applicable to Macao," he said. "Most of them will get
renewal after 1999 so long as they will help Macao's economic
development, social stability and suit the status of Macao itself."
</P>
<P>
Wang said that the two sides reached consensus on Macao's
renewal into the International Organization of Consumers' Unions
after 1999 in today's meeting, adding that both sides are
satisfied with the working process in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Mendes, representative of the Portuguese side, said that
the two sides have exchanged views on the list of 200 world bodies
and conventions applicable to Macao, and both agree to do the best
to quicken the working procedure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
