<HEADLINE> Universities In East China Province Boost Scientific Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang province
has benefited a lot from scientific research by schools of higher
learning in local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang University has been focusing on high technology
research to provide support for the local economy.
</P>
<P>
Many research findings by its professors were considered to be
of great importance in 1996 and were given top awards by the
provincial government.
</P>
<P>
The university is an example of relying on intellectuals to
help speed up economic take-off.
</P>
<P>
Another university, Zhejiang Industry University, has succeeded
in the development of a synthetic catalyst, a world class endeavor
of its kind which has won a national award.
</P>
<P>
Scholars and doctors at Zhejiang Medical University, the only
higher learning facility of medical science in the economically
developed province, have produced a new remedy for liver ailments.
</P>
<P>
"Colleges and universities in Zhejiang province have been
playing a major role in scientific research and technological
renovation," said an official at the province's education
committee.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological research programs carried out by
universities accounted for 57 among the 300 programs carried out
throughout the province last year.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,000 scientific achievements from the universities have
been applied in the Hangzhou-Jiaxing-Huzhou Hi-tech Pilot
Development Zone, in the northeastern part of the province where
industry and agriculture have seen a very rapid growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
