<HEADLINE> Philippines Named as Best Bond Issuer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Europe-based international
finance publication Euromoney has named the Philippines as Asia's
best sovereign bond issuer for its 690-million-U.S.-dollar Brady
bond exchange offer in 1996, the Philippine News Agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Philippines has recently retired 1.9
billion dollars of its Brady bond, floated during the tenure of
former President Corazon Aquino to generate support for the
country's sagging economy, by exchanging them with new
non-collateralized 20-year bonds.
</P>
<P>
The exchange allowed the Philippines to slash off 84 million
dollars from its 35-billion-dollar foreign debt, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Euromoney also named five Philippine corporate bond issuers as
among the "best or most professional issuers" in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The international publication named Ayala Corporation as the
best issuer in the Philippines; Filinvest, Inc. as the overall
best convertible; PCIBank as the best bank issuer; Philippine Long
Distance Telephone Co. as the best telecommunications firm issuer;
and SM Prime Holdings as the overall best new issuer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
