<HEADLINE> First Foreigner Granted Post-doctorate Degree in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Stobbe Helge from Germany has
become the first foreigner to receive a post-doctorate in chemical
engineering at a Chinese university.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Helge got his Ph.D. at Essen University in Germany in
1993. While sorting through materials on international education,
he learned that Beijing Chemical Industry University was the
leader in liquid film separation techniques.
</P>
<P>
He came to the Beijing-based university in September, 1994, and
began research on protein separation, working jointly with other
specialists.
</P>
<P>
After two years of study and research, Helge passed the
assessment of six professors who said he showed creativity in his
work to separate protein by using liquid film separation
techniques.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Chemical Industry University is one of the
country's major universities, having 15 programs at the masters
level, four at the Ph.D. level, and two for post-doctorates.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 100 foreigners are enrolled in
post-graduate studies at the university. 
</P>
</TEXT>
