<HEADLINE> Highway Links up All Townships in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province, famous for
its fable of the "foolish old man who removed the mountains,"
built a record 2,200 kilometers of highway last year.
</P>
<P>
The roads enabled all of the 2,400 townships in the province to
be linked.
</P>
<P>
The total length of highway opened to traffic in the province
now stretches over 50,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The newly operational highways include 94 kilometers of express
way, 350 kilometers of second-grade highways, and 1,800 kilometers
of county and township roads.
</P>
<P>
Apart from utilizing state funds for major highway projects,
Henan, a center for China's highway network, collected 2.2 billion
yuan (275 million U.S. dollars) from society for local highway
construction in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The collected tolls will be used to pay back investors and
loans, with the rest of the money used for further road building.
</P>
<P>
Counties in northwest and southwest mountain areas made the
most hard efforts in building highways and bridges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
