<HEADLINE> More Nationwide Science Organizations Set up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of nationwide
science associations and societies is on the rise in China and
they have become an important part of the country's scientific and
technological promoting force.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent national conference sponsored by the
China Association for Science and Technology, China now boasts 165
national science associations and societies, covering almost all
academic fields.
</P>
<P>
Among these organizations, there are 39 that focus on natural
science, 62 on engineering, 13 on agricultural science, 22 on
medicine, and 29 in overlapping fields or for science
popularization.
</P>
<P>
Experts claim these specialized associations and societies vary
in academic areas and are highly qualified.
</P>
<P>
They publish 457 kinds of academic and science popularization
journals, serve as members in 252 international science and
technology organizations, hold 3,000 domestic academic seminars
and over 100 international meetings.
</P>
<P>
One survey shows that between 1978 and the end of last year,
the national organizations had sponsored more than 40,000 academic
activities attracting six million participants, making these
organizations the pillars of academic exchange in and out of China.
</P>
<P>
These organs have also mobilized expert teams to go to the
countryside to popularize science knowledge and train some 100
million farmers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
