<HEADLINE> Test Tube Baby Born in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A test tube baby boy has been
born in a hospital attached to the Hainan Medical College, in
south China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Hainan's first ever test tube baby weighed 3.2 kg at birth and
appeared to be healthy, according to nurses of the hospital.
</P>
<P>
The hospital began test tube fertilization research in October
1995, and successfully inseminated and nurtured the test tube baby
in May last year.
</P>
<P>
The first test tube baby in China was born in March 1988. Up to
now, only eight hospitals across the country are able to provide
the technique involved.  
</P>
