<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign exchange control,
labor market flexibility, infrastructure and how to meet budget
deficit goals were high on the agenda in the weekend top meeting
of the ruling African National Congress (ANC) in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The three-day closed-door meeting, attended by national and
provincial ANC leaders, was the start of the systematic pulling
together of the party's policies to ensure the achievement of its
social and economic goals, the "The Citizen" paper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Labor Minister Tito Mboweni was quoted as saying Tuesday that
a common understanding had to be reached on a labor market
flexibility with security promoting social justice and avoiding
right-wing policies for deregulation of the labor market.
</P>
