<HEADLINE> China Sets Ambitious Goals for Electronics Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China has set new goals for its
electronics industry this year, aiming to score a gross output
value of 360 billion yuan in 1997, up 20 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
According a national meeting on the electronics industry that
opened here today, the industry will reap total sales of 240
billion yuan this year, up 23 percent; and earn 24 billion US
dollars from exports, up 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the electronics industry scored a gross output value
of 298.2 billion yuan, up 20.7 percent; and made sales of 194.7
billion yuan, up 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
Output of investment-based products, including computers and
telecommunications equipment, shot up 40 percent last year. And
the total foreign trade volume hit 34.63 billion US dollars,
including 18.97 billion dollars in exports in the January-November
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that competition in the electronics market is
becoming increasingly fierce with name brand products gaining a
lion's share of the market.  
</P>
