<HEADLINE> First Foreign-funded Lubricating Oil Venture Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The first exclusively
foreign-funded lubricating oil and grease blending plant has gone
into operation in Tianjin, the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
The plant, covering 50,000 sq. m. at the Nanjiang Development
Zone near Tianjin Harbor, was built by the Mobil Petroleum
Co. Ltd. of the United States at a cost of 45 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
It will annually produce 45,000 tons of lubricating oil in 23
varieties, and 5,000 tons of lubricating grease in three
varieties. Its products will be sold in north and northeast China.
</P>
<P>
This coastal city has become the fountainhead of many
prestigious transnational petrochemical companies in recent
years. In 1994, Esso, the largest oil company in the United
States, invested 30 million US dollars to build a lubricating oil
blending plant.
</P>
<P>
The Shell 0il Company followed suit, building four
petrochemical works in the southern part of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin will become a rising petrochemical center when all
these foreign-funded projects start operation, said an official of
the Tianjin Harbor Administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
