<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Becomes China's Major Iron, Steel Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has become one of China's major producers of iron and
steel with its output ranking third and second in the country.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that Hebei's metallurgical industry
generated an output value totalling 15.43 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Its output of steel reached 8.64 million tons last year, up
nearly 20 percent over the previous year; that of pig iron 12
million tons, up 16 percent; and that of rolled steel 6.2 million
tons, up almost 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The metallurgical industry obtained sales income amounting to
24.3 billion yuan, and generated profits and taxes totalling 2.36
billion yuan last year. 
</P>
