<HEADLINE> Beijing Shows Strong Momentum in Machinery and Electronic Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The export of machinery and
electronic products in the Chinese capital city of Beijing
maintained a strong growing momentum last year.
</P>
<P>
Despite Beijing's slump in exports as a whole, the export
volume of machinery and electronic products reached 740 million US
dollars, an increase of 18 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The city has been carrying out a supportive policy in these
trades to nurture a large number of competent and competitive
factories and foreign trade companies.
</P>
<P>
Large quantities of color kinescopes, integrated circuits,
videocassette players, telecommunications equipment, vehicles,
machine tools, and other machinery and electronic devices have
been exported to areas around the globe.
</P>
<P>
According to the city's Ninth Five-year Plan (1996-2000), the
export of machinery and electronic products is expected to reach
1.2 billion US dollars by the year 2000, which will account for 30
percent of the city's overall export trade.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this goal, the city is striving to establish 20
businesses which are able to produce popular export products.
</P>
