<HEADLINE> Hebei Adopts Regulation to Guide Tourism Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A new tourism law went
into effect in Hebei province, north China, today which will
regulate the development and protection of tourism resources and
management, and spell out the rights and duties of tourists.
</P>
<P>
The Hebei regulation on tourism, adopted by the 22nd session of
the Standing Committee of the Eighth Provincial People Congress,
is China's fourth local law of the kind.
</P>
<P>
The new regulation welcomes overseas companies, organizations
or individuals to join in the development of Hebei's tourism
resources and the building of tourism facilities.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xinyong, Deputy Director of the Hebei Tourism Bureau, said
that compared with other big tourism sites in China, his province
has lagged behind, adding that Hebei's development of tourism
resources and management level could not meet the needs of the
nationwide expansion of the sector.
</P>
<P>
He said that the poor management of some scenic spots has
damaged Hebei's image and has adversely affected provincial
tourism.
</P>
<P>
Hebei, which surrounds China's capital city of Beijing, and the
big industrial city of Tianjin, faces the Bohai Sea and has rich
tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Hebei received 260,000 overseas tourists and 28
million domestic tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
