<HEADLINE> China's Electronic Products Market to Top 1 Trillion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- China's market potential for
electronic products is expected to top one trillion yuan in the
year 2000, and six trillion yuan just ten years later.
</P>
<P>
According to a national meeting on the electronics industry,
which opened in Beijing today, China has a huge market for
electronic products, with an annual growth rate as high as 30
percent expected.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that with the quickening of the
information-oriented process and the improvement of living
standards, people are posing greater demands on electronic
products.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has already designated electronics as a
pillar industry of the national economy, and designated electronic
and information products as new sectors for development, which
will push ahead the national economy at a fast pace.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of the Electronics Industry, China
will boost the development of promising products such as
large-scale integrated circuits, computers, software, computer
networks, mobile telecommunications, digital program-controlled
switchboards and large-screen color televisions.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary estimates show that the market capacity of the
growth products alone is expected to hit 400-500 billion yuan by
the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
Electronic products associated with automobiles, energy,
transportation, machinery, medicine and education will also enjoy
bright prospects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
