<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Preparing for Travelers to and from Hongkong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Transport departments in
Guangzhou are gearing for a massive exodus of people by public
transport between the city and Hong Kong during the Spring
Festival, which falls on the 7th of next month.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, will handle almost 12 million travelers over
the holiday period, up 1.1 percent over last year. A substantial
increase is expected in the number of people journeying between
Guangzhou and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In addition to four regular trains between the two places, the
city will add another train to cater for the extra passengers,
with a combined capacity of 3,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Baiyun Airport now has five flights to Hong Kong every day, and
plans more if demand increases.
</P>
<P>
Local transport authorities say 14 sea voyages will operate
daily during the Spring Festival period from Guangzhou to Hong
Kong, with more than 3,800 seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
