<HEADLINE> Shanghai Petrochemical Company Raises Funds on Hong Kong Bourse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Petrochemical
Co. Ltd. recently issued 150 million H shares on the Hong Kong
stock market and pooled 342 million Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to an executive of the company, each share was sold
for 2.28 Hong Kong dollars on January 6, and all shares sold out
in one hour.
</P>
<P>
The company also issued 500 million H shares on the Hong Kong
bourse last August. All money raised from the issues will be used
to expand the company's ethylene project with a production
capacity of 300,000 tons, and to cover the capital needed for
maintaining operations.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the company, a leading tax contributor in China's
petrochemical sector, refined 4.85 million tons of crude oil and
produced 465,000 tons of ethylene, accounting for one sixth of the
country's total ethylene production.
</P>
<P>
It also generated 8.15 billion yuan (one U.S. dollar equals to
8.3 Chinese yuan) of total industrial output value according to
constant prices in 1990, up 13.9 percent over 1995 level.
</P>
<P>
The company was placed first on the list of the "best
management companies of China" by Asian Monetary Magazine in a
program to select the leading firms among those listed on the Hong
Kong bourse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
