<HEADLINE> Japanese Enterprises to Build Industrial Park in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Over 100 enterprises in Fukui
Prefecture of Japan will jointly fund an industrial park in
Shaoxing City, east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the Fukui Chamber of Commerce and Industry, some
110 enterprises in Fukui have selected Shaoxing as an ideal
investment spot, as Shaoxing is a textile industrial base in
China, and chemical fiber and dying are pillar industries in Fukui.
</P>
<P>
Chamber officials believe the two areas can benefit each other
in terms of funding, technology, management and markets.
</P>
<P>
The industrial park, to be built in the Shaoxing Economic
Development Zone in three years, will cover an area of 250,000 sq
m.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for foreign enterprises to independently
build an industrial park in Zhejiang, according to provincial
officials.
</P>
<P>
Fukui and Zhejiang forged friendly ties in 1990. The Fukui
Chamber of Commerce and Industry expressed the intention of
building an industrial park in Zhejiang last year and received
positive responses from such cities as Ningbo, Xiaoshan and
Hangzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
