<HEADLINE> Land Reclamation in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,550 square km of
polder (shore land) has been reclaimed in east China's
densely-populated Zhejiang Province in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The area accounts for one-fifth of the total acreage reclaimed
in China during the period.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has planned to develop 16,500 ha of
polder in the coming five years. Under the plan, various
departments will try to avoid adverse effects on the environment
in the course of the reclamation.
</P>
<P>
The province now leads the country in reclamation technology.
</P>
