<HEADLINE> Indian Pilot Dies in Mig-29 Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- An Indian air force Mig-29
fighter crashed near the Pune air base in Maharashtra state, south
India, on Tuesday, killing the pilot, the Times of India reported
today.
</P>
<P>
This takes the number of the Russian-made Mig-29s lost so far
to five while the total tally of aircraft lost by the air force in
the last three years has risen to 79.
</P>
<P>
This total loss figure adds up to more than four squadrons'
worth of aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Confirming the accident on Tuesday, an Indian Defense Ministry
spokesman said the fighter had crashed while landing after a
routine sortie.
</P>
<P>
A report from Pune said that the Mig-29 has crashed into a
stone quarry near the air base.
</P>
<P>
The pilot, C.D. Chardrashekhar, was air officer commanding of
the air base and had flown 5,600 hours.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the crash remains unclear.  
</P>
