<HEADLINE> EDS-more details added Chinese President Meets Congolese Defense Minister in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said that Sino-Congolese long-term and steady relations and
overall cooperation oriented toward the 21st century are bound to
be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Congolese Defense Minister Francois
Ayayen this morning, Jiang said that although China and the Congo
are separated geographically, the two peoples have enjoyed
traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Congo is one of the first African countries to
form diplomatic relations with China, Jiang said that since the
two countries forged the ties over 30 years ago, bilateral
relations have developed smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have cooperated successfully in the political,
economic, cultural and military fields, and the two peoples have
formed a deep friendship, added Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the world situation has experienced many
changes, Sino-Congolese friendship and cooperation have always
developed steadily, and withstood the test of time.
</P>
<P>
Ayayen said that his country attaches importance to the
development of traditional two-way friendship, hoping that
bilateral friendship and cooperation in various fields can be
further solidified.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Congolese government, considering Taiwan as
an inalienable part of the Chinese territory, adheres to a "one
China" position and supports China's great cause of a peaceful
reunification.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation for Ayayen's statement, Jiang
wished that under the leadership of Congolese President Pascal
Lissouba, the Congolese people would continue to score new
achievements in safeguarding national stability, developing the
economy and strengthening military construction.
</P>
<P>
Also present at today's meeting was Chi Haotian, vice-chairman
of China's Central Military Commission, State Councillor and
Minister of National Defense.
</P>
<P>
Ayayen is here as Chi's guest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
