<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muster Enters Australian Open Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Fifth-seeded Thomas Muster
surprised his higher ranked opponents Goran Ivanisevic with a
straight-set victory at the Australian Open quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Muster, a clay court expert, won the match 6-4, 6-2, 6-3 over
his third-seeded Croatian opponent to enter the semi-finals of the
grand slam.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic was nervous in the match and made a lot of
mistakes. That cost he the chance of winning his first ever grand
slam title.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic has been in the top 10 for the past five years but
has never won any of the four grand slam championships.
</P>
<P>
Muster proved that he could play good tennis though he was not
on clay courts. He served well and dominated the match from the
baseline.
</P>
<P>
Muster will play either world number one Pete Sampras or
10th-seeded Albert Costa of Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
