<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Expecting Birth of its 200 Millionth Baby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
prepared a surprise present for the country's 200 millionth baby
who is expected to be born on February 4, Population Minister
Haryono Suyono said.
</P>
<P>
"The 200 millionth baby will get a surprise present from the
government," he told a coordinating meeting on people's welfare
here Tuesday, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Haryono said each province could nominate its 200 millionth
baby to represent it in an Indonesian child selection.
</P>
<P>
He said the child to be selected as the 200 millionth baby
would have to be one who was not delivered through a Cesarean
section, whose parents were legally married and whose mother got
married and gave birth to her first baby when she was more than 20
years old.
</P>
<P>
The baby could be the married couple's first, second or third
child but in case it was the second or third child, its mother
would have had delivered each of her children after
sufficiently-long intervals.
</P>
<P>
Among other requirements was that the mother of the baby would
have had her pregnancy or pregnancies examined regularly at a
health care center, by a doctor or a midwife, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
