<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainian President Calls for Economic Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
says the country must carry out its economic reform policy this
year based on a stable financial situation and decreased inflation.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma made the remarks today at the sixth session of Ukraine's
Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs. He used to be one of
the co-presidents of the Union, which offered much support to his
economic reform policies.
</P>
<P>
The new policy would try to stimulate production on the basis
of financial stability, Kuchma said.
</P>
<P>
The primary task of the government in the new year was to take
measures to develop medium-sized and small businesses, to remove
barriers to the privatization drive and put effective bankruptcy
mechanisms into operation.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma pointed out that the tax reform, now being carried out,
would relax the government's tax pressure and be important in
stimulating production and securing the funds granted to
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
