<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Backs Romania For First NATO Intake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 21 (Xinhua) -- France is proposing that
Romania be first in the group of East European countries to join
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Michel Barnier, a representative at ministerial level in charge
of European affairs at the French Foreign Ministry, told a press
conference today that his country supported Romania because it was
qualified in politics and had a consolidated legal system.
</P>
<P>
Barnier was here to make preparations for French President
Jacques Chirac's visit to Romania on February 20-22. Chirac will
be the second French president to visit the country, following
President Charles de Gaulle's visit in May 1968.
</P>
<P>
He said Chirac would discuss with the Romanian president the
possibility of cooperation in the economy, defense and diplomacy.
</P>
</TEXT>
