<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Upgrade Container Handling Capacity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 22 (Xinhua) -- The Yangon port authority has
imported two 35-ton gantry cranes from Japan in an effort to
upgrade the port's container handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
Yangon port, Myanmar's main gateway to the world, handles all
of its imports and over 90 percent of exports.
</P>
<P>
The port handled 73,198 containers in 1995-96 up from 44,790 in
1994-95 and over 7.037 million tons of cargo in 1995-96 up from
6.541 million tons in 1993-94, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, four container wharves are being built at Thilawa
port, a newly established one near Yangon port with investment
from Singapore. Of which the first 330-meter-long wharf had been
completed and put into service early this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
