<HEADLINE> 400 Taken Ill After Gas Leakage in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 22 (Xinhua) -- About 400 people were taken
ill after they inhaled ammonia gas which leaked from a tanker
after it fell into a ditch in India's Madhya Pradesh on Tuesday,
the Times of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said because of the gas leakage, many people,
mostly farmers and construction workers, suffered a burning
sensation in the eyes and vomited.
</P>
<P>
Those affected by the gas leakage were treated and later
discharged from a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Traffic on the road where the tanker overturned was suspended
for three hours, the sources said, adding that the spot was away
from residential areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
