<HEADLINE> Bosnia Continues Trial of Izethegovic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia's Banja Luka court
continued the trial by default today of Alija Izethegovic, who
heads the Presidency of the Republic of Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Izethegovic is accused of being a war criminal and charged with
killing civilians, the wounded and prisoners of war. On December
24, the Banja Luka court opened the first court session to try
Izethegovic, who has refused to appear.
</P>
<P>
