<HEADLINE> U.S. Experts Begin Training Bosnia's Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Military experts from the
United States began to train the first group of officers of
Bosnia's Muslim-Croat Federation Army today at a military base
close to the Bosnian capital of Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the U.S. program to train and equip the
federation army, which will cost 400 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, the first consignment of ammunition
provided by the United States was shipped to Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Under the program of the U.S. experts, the weaponry of the
federation army would be double that of the Serb forces, namely
273 tanks, 227 armored vehicles, 41 fighters, 14 helicopters and
1,000 artillery units.
</P>
<P>
The start of the training program also means the official
establishment of the federation army, which should contain 30,000
to 35,000 troops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
