<HEADLINE> Ukraine's Nonaligned Status Unchanged, FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian foreign minister Gennady
Udovenko said today that the nonaligned status is a strategic
policy adopted by Ukraine, and any change of the position was
"unsuitable" at the present time.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking at a news briefing following a claim, once
again, by the Mayor of Moscow, Yuri Luzhkov, that the port city of
Sevastopol was in the past, and would be in the future, Russia's.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko stressed that the nonaligned position was Ukraine's
"most correct choice", which "completely conforms to the present
reality".
</P>
<P>
Mayor Luzhkov made his remarks last Friday when attending a
handing over ceremony of houses financed by Russia for sailors of
Russia's Black Sea Fleet.
</P>
<P>
His remarks caused strong repercussions and the Ukrainian
foreign ministry delivered a protest note to the Russian
government.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko said that though some Russian politicians recently
took part in unfriendly activities against Ukraine, and made
speeches damaging Ukraine's territorial integrity, Ukraine would
steadfastly carry the strategic policy of being nonaligned.
</P>
</TEXT>
