<HEADLINE> Kyrgyzstan Continues Economic Reform in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyzstan is to continue a
second phase of economic reform in 1997 so as to help complete its
transformation to a market economy, says Kyrgyz Prime Minister
Apas Jumagulov.
</P>
<P>
The reform would continue reconstructing the national economy,
which was damaged in 1991-95, to perfect a market economic system
started during the first phase of economic reform last year.
</P>
<P>
Jumagulov was quoted today by an Interfax news agency report
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Other major tasks to be covered this year were agrarian reform,
privatization and modernization of enterprises and the creation of
favorable conditions for small-scale enterprises, Jumagulov said.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that his country would spare no efforts in
promoting the economic integration process within the Commonwealth
of Independent States. 
</P>
