<HEADLINE> Brazil Reports $5.5 Billion Trade Deficit In 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil had a 5.539 billion
U.S. dollar trade deficit in 1996, Brazil's Finance Ministry
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian exports totaled of 47.747 billion dollars in 1996
while its imports were 53.286 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last December the trade deficit was 1.787 billion dollars, with
5.576 billion dollars of imports versus 3.789 billion dollars of
exports.
</P>
<P>
Jose Roberto Mendoca, economic policy secretary for the Finance
Ministry, said that the 1996 deficit was mainly due to increased
imports of raw materials, capital goods and fuel. 
</P>
