<HEADLINE> Cuba to Commemorate Guevara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Cuban Communist Party (CCP)
leaders will set up a commission to coordinate this year's
activities that will pay homage to Ernesto "Che" Guevara and
his comrades who were all killed in action.
</P>
<P>
The commission will be chaired by Jose Ramon Machado Ventura
with Jose Ramon Balaguer as vice-chairman, both members of the
CCP's politburo, said the official newspaper "Granma" today.
</P>
<P>
General Harry Villegas, Che's chief bodyguard during the
revolutionary war in Cuba and a member of the guerrilla staff in
Bolivia as well as the author of a book on that Argentine-Cuban
fighter will also serve as a vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
Rolando Alfonso Borges, who heads the ideological department of
the CCP's Central Committee will be the secretary of the national
commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission will coordinate the main acts of homage to Che
and his comrades-in-arms and will approve all the programs and
measures of a national character of other political organizations
and the masses and pertinent state institutions.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will also be in charge of preserving the political,
military and cultural heritage of the life and works of Che
Guevara. 
</P>
