have shown interest to invest in the MSC which is intended to
create a perfect environment for companies wanting to develop and
distribute multimedia products and service.
</P>
<P>
He also chaired the inaugural International Advisory Panel
(IAP) meeting on the MSC at Stanford University, California.
</P>
<P>
The IAP is composed of top leaders in the information
technology industry including Microsoft founder Bill Gates and
Apply chairman Gilbert Amelio.
</P>
<P>
In Japan, Mahathir met chief executive officers of Japanese
corporate bodies in that field.
</P>
<P>
A number of Japanese companies including Japanese giant Nippon
Telegraph and Telephone Corporation (NTT) also indicated their
keenness to make investment in the MSC.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said vast opportunities will open up for all with the
development of the MSC, hoping all parties concerned, including
land owners and government employees, would cooperate to
accelerate the development.  
