<HEADLINE> Maxims of Chinese Revolutionary Veterans Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 22 (Xinhua) -- A book containing the maxims of
China's revolutionary veterans, either deceased or alive, is now
available to the public.
</P>
<P>
The principles were passed down from older generations of
Chinese revolutionary veterans such as Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai, Liu
Shaoqi, Zhu De, Deng Xiaoping and Chen Yun. Most of the ideas were
selected from their collected works.
</P>
<P>
The veteran statesmen left behind a large quantity of valuable
sayings depicting their persistent pursuit of communism, their
active exploration and deep meditation about the revolution and
construction in China, and their codes of exemplary conduct they
believed would support the people's cause.
</P>
<P>
The book was compiled by the Party Literature Research Center
of the Communist Party of the China Central Committee and
published jointly by the Central Literature Publishing House and
the Shanghai People's Publishing House. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
