<DOCNO> XIE19970122.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiamen to Adjust Priority of Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen, one of China's Special
Economic Zones, plans to adjust its priorities in foreign
investment to basic and infrastructure projects this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the local government, the strongest emphasis will
be placed on agriculture, and agriculture projects, including
farming, breeding, and farm-product processing will receive
government funding.
</P>
<P>
With its advantageous location near Taiwan, the city will focus
more on attracting investment from that region this year.
</P>
<P>
The city will select a group of projects to be negotiated with
Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, more overseas funds will be directed toward some 1,000
infrastructure projects, which are associated with the current
3,800 companies now in operation. The local government has chosen
the first batch of 50 such projects.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the city had approved more than 3,800
projects with total investment of 15 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
