<HEADLINE> World Champion Takes Lead at Monte Carlo Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 21 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tommi Makinen of
Finland took over the overall lead after Tuesday's stages at the
Monte Carlo rally.
</P>
<P>
Makinen, driving a Mitsubishi, began the penultimate day three
seconds behind leader Carlos Sainz of Spain. He put up a splendid
performance on Tuesday and ended the day with a 24-second lead.
</P>
<P>
Piero Liatti of Italy ranked second overall while Sainz was
third with 27 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Colin McRae of Britain crashed out of the race after starting
the day in the fourth place.
</P>
<P>
Three-times winner Didier Auriol of France was also forced to
retire with gearbox problems.
</P>
<P>
The rally will end after six more timed stages on Wednesday.
