<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Wipes out Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 22 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, a leading industrial
city in north China has succeeded in eradicating poverty four
years ahead of the national target set by the central government.
</P>
<P>
The per capita net income of farmers in 175 poor villages in
rural Tianjin soared to 1,550 yuan by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
This was the result of an anti-poverty program launched in
1993, under which the municipal government provided these areas
with financial aid, technical guidance and materials to help them
develop local economy.
</P>
<P>
The combined grain output of the villages increased by 1.35
times in the past three years. The outputs of vegetables, fruit,
poultry, eggs and meat also grew by a wide margin.
</P>
<P>
In the course of industrial restructuring, the ratio of
industry and service trade has increased, and the overall capacity
of agriculture has been strengthened, said a local official.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
