<HEADLINE> UAE President Says Fighting in Sudan Is Internal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
(UAE) President Zayed Bin Sultan al Nahyan said today that the
fighting in Sudan was an internal affair and his country prepared
to help the Sudanese people to reach a settlement.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks during his meeting with Sudan's
visiting Minister of Cabinet Presidency Amid Al Rakni Bahri who
conveyed him a letter from Sudanese President Omar Hassan Ahmed
al-Bashir.
</P>
<P>
"What is happening in Sudan is an internal affair and if our
Sudanese brothers ask for our help, we will prepare to do it," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Fightings between Sudanese government army and opposition
troops have continued for days in eastern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The president also said that any foreign effort to divide Sudan
is "unacceptable" and if the Sudanese people can not resolve their
dispute by themselves, "they should ask for help from their Arab
brothers."
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese government has accused Ethiopia and Eritrea for
aiding the opposition forces, a charge both countries have
denied. But the rebel side has ruled out a foreign intervention.
</P>
<P>
The president also called for an Arab reconciliation and said
the Arab world should not "keep silent" if anything happens in an
Arab state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
