<HEADLINE> Future Muslim-Croat Federation Army Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The training of a first group
of officers of the future Muslim-Croat Federation army has started
in Hadzici near Sarajevo under the supervision of U.S. military
experts.
</P>
<P>
The training is the first step in the complicated process of
creating a joint Muslim-Croat army which should comprise 30,000 to
35,000 professional soldiers in line with the orders of the
federation's political leadership, according to a Tanjug news
agency report from Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
The federal army is expected to have a joint artillery
division, a helicopter force, anti-aircraft defense and rapid
intervention force.
</P>
<P>
The army will comprise three Muslim and one Croat corps with 14
brigades -- 10 Muslim and four Croat.
</P>
<P>
According to U.S. training plans, the federation army armaments
should be twice as large as those of the army of the other entity
in Bosnia -- Republika Srpska. 
</P>
</TEXT>
